<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900907-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>900907-0026.</DOCID><HL>   What's News --   Business and Finance</HL><DATE>09/07/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A1</SO><LP>   WORLD OIL PRICES SURGED on pessimism over the Mideastcrisis and the outlook for winter supplies. Speculativebuying helped push some crude prices beyond $31 a barrel. Thejump came even as some small producers planned to follow OPECin raising output. Stocks fell, with the Dow Jonesindustrials drop ping 31.93 points to 2596.29. Tokyo andLondon shares declined as well.   ---</LP><TEXT>   Equimark's Alan Fellheimer resigned as chairman of thetroubled bank holding concern. The move follows the Tischfamily's disclosure that it holds a 6.8% stake in the firm.   ---   Franklin Savings' return to its previous management fromcontrol of federal regulators was blocked by a U.S. court'stemporary stay.   ---   The major U.S. retailers posted modest sales gains. Butanalysts say weakness in home furnishings and early fallmerchandise indicate diffi culties through the winter season.   ---   U.S. businesses are paring capital-spending plans becauseof growing concern about the economy, the latest CommerceDepartment survey in dicates. Outlays for 1990 are now expected to increase 5.4%, down from the previous estimate of6.8%.   ---   G-7 officials will meet in Paris next week to discuss thedollar's recent decline and consider if actions are needed tobolster the currency.   ---   U.S. bank earnings fell 24% in the second quarter to $5.3billion, largely on a $1.9 billion jump in Northeasterninstitutions' loan-loss reserves. Bad real estate loansremain the major problem for the industry.   ---   Both parties' leaders vowed to present separate $50billion deficit-reduction packages as their opening bids inrenewed budget talks today.   ---   Motorola plans to start shipping its much-delayed 68040microproces sor in October. The delays have in turn set backproduction at computer makers that rely on the chip.   ---   Lotus Development is issuing the latest upgrade to its1-2-3 spread sheet, a move that could help reverse thecompany's earnings difficulties.                                                                                                          IBM announced a joint venture with Metaphor Computer toproduce an underlying layer of software aimed at speedingdevelopment of personal-computer software uses.   ---   L.A. Gear expects to post fiscal third-quarter profitbelow that of a year ago, when the sneaker maker reported arecord net of $22 million.   ---   Goodyear expects to post a third-quarter loss of about $65million mostly related to 1,180 planned layoffs in itsEuropean operations. The tire maker also expressed concernover adverse effects on raw material costs due to the Mideastcrisis.   ---   Markets --   Stocks: Volume 125,620,000 shares. Dow Jones industrials2596.29, off 31.93; transportation 892.20, off 5.54;utilities 198.25, off 0.19.   Bonds: Shearson Lehman Brothers Treasury index 3350.65, up5.68.   Commodities: Dow Jones futures index 133.55, up 0.37; spotindex 130.10, up 0.13.   Dollar: 140.70 yen, off 1.00; 1.5550 marks, off 0.0035.</TEXT></DOC>